#note Q wants me to play TEENY for 10 more points and blocking a lot more. It seemed counter-productive to close the board holding the blank, but it does cut Gitonga's bingo percentage from 20% to 12%. After YE I bingo 90% of the time versus 56% of the time after TEENY, but Quackle is in no rush to cash the blank. In general, making fishy plays with the blank is a bad idea if there aren't extenuating circumstances - the blank cleans up a lot of bad draws.
